      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLITZBURG (6) had been knocking on the door before finding the grade too tough at Doomben. Has strong relative numbers and gets some gear switched. On a quick backup, and this is a suitable assignment. SLIPPIN' JIMMY (1) is a distance specialist who bounced back last start by a head as the public elect over 1100m at Ipswich. Suitably placed, anticipating another big run. POSEIDON'S SON (4) made it four wins in a row last time out when he scored by 0.6 lengths over 1175m at Grafton. Has been heavily bet and is in a sharp yard. Likely to be in the finish again. SAILOR'S SECRET (2) raced close to the lead before clearing out to score an effortless 2.25 lengths win over 1400m at this track last time. Keeps the handy 2kg claim and has to be included in calculations.BADGERS NUTS (3) just missed the hat-trick at Ipswich first-up when expected to need it. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and is in the mix.",
